    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to painted, photographic, or sculptural portraits that are created by combining multiple parts to make a face, including images where objects such as books, vegetable matter, or other images are combined to form physiognomic constructions. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047003/Margolin, Stalin and Wheat, Gastronomica (2003)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047000/Burson, Seeing and Believing (2002)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047001/Wind, Studies in Allegorical Portraiture, Journal of the Warburg Institute (1937)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar geschilderde, fotografische of gebeeldhouwde portretten die worden gecreëerd door het combineren van objecten zoals boeken, plantaardig materiaal of meerdere afbeeldingen tot fysionomische constructies.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指稱結合多重部份以形成面部的繪畫、相片或雕塑肖像，包括組合諸如書籍、蔬菜類植物或其他圖像而構成的面像結構。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bezieht sich auf ein gemaltes, photografisches oder bildhauerisches Porträt, bei dem ein Gesicht durch Verbinden mehrerer Teile gestaltet ist, einschließlich Bilder, bei denen Objekte wie Bücher, pflanzliches Material oder andere Bilder verbunden werden, um physiognomische Strukturen zu formen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
